Perception, memory, learning, prediction, explanation, and communication all depend on interpreting incomplete evidence to infer hidden structure.

One connection I think is especially strong with your recent additions is that Kurage, Cherenkov, and Semantic LiDAR are already interpretability operators. Kurage interprets the state of the semantic medium, Cherenkov interprets unseen sources from their disturbances, and Semantic LiDAR interprets hidden structure by probing and measuring reflections. Framed this way, interpretability isn’t just another subsystem—it becomes a unifying scientific discipline within Pantheon for reconstructing latent structure from observable signals.